&gt; Generally, voice recognition software requires the user to go through several training phases with it before using it, so the software is able to recognize that particular users words (unless it is a VERY limited set of words). So with this kind of software, it would be hard to create an objective training session to pull a voice sequence out of noise from a voice that it has never heard. The software would make a lot of mistakes, and perhaps even be subject to paradolia, just like people.
